The two British singers are set to perform onstage at the British music industry’s Brit Awards, February 21, 2018, reports The Sun. The headliners will be joined by Stormzy and Dua Lipa. “Castle On The Hill” singer, Ed Sheeran, also took to the stage at the 2017 ceremony, performing a remix of his hit “Shape Of You” with Stormzy. The ceremony will be held at London’s O2 Arena and hosted by British comedian Jack Whitewall. The 2018 awards trophies are designed by British-Indian sculptor Anish Kapoor. The Brit Awards are the British equivalent of the USA’s Grammy Awards. -Relaxnews